Title: Ayurveda Essentials 100% Natural Color Shade Dried Rose Petals(100 g)
Description: Beauty benefits of rose petalsIn fact, it is said that ancient Greeks and Romans used rose petals to perfume their baths. Here's looking at the beauty benefits of this fragrant flower and how you can include rose water, rose oil and rose petals in your skin and hair care routine.> Skin toner: Rose water is considered to be a natural toner for your skin. Once you return home from work, take a swab of cotton dipped in rose water and gently wipe your face in a circular motion. This will help get rid of the dirt as well as makeup.> Soothes skin: The natural oils found in roses help retain moisture in the skin. This results in your skin feeling smooth and soft. The sugars in rose petals especially benefit those with sensitive skin.> Acts as sunscreen: A rich source of vitamin C, rose petals act as an excellent sunblock. Make a lotion by mixing cucumber juice, glycerin and rose water and apply it on your skin before heading out in the sun.> Helps fight acne: The anti-bacterial properties found in rose makes it amazing for fighting acne and breakouts. Rose water can also help soothe irritated skin and reduce its redness. It is also known to heal skin ailments like eczema and psoriasis.> Prevent dark circles: Soak thin swabs of cotton in rose water and put them on your eyes to prevent dark circles.> Mood lifting properties: In a bad mood or feel the stress? Known as a powerful mood enhancer, add rose petals to a warm bath will help you get rid of feelings of anxiety. Apart from being a detox for your body, it will also help you sleep better.> Nourishes scalp: Rose water is great for your hair as heals the itchy and flaky areas of your scalp. Moreover, it helps increase blood flow to the hair follicles, promoting hair growth.

Title: Healthgenie BP Monitor Cuff Bp Monitor Cuff
Description: Healthgenie Blood Pressure Monitor Cuff Size EXTRA LARGE It is important to use an appropriate size in order to obtain accurate blood pressure reading. This monitor cuff has a size 30-42 cms, 11.8 -16.5 inch (XL). It is suitable for all healthgenie Blood pressure monitors. It can easily be inserted into the monitor. This cuff pack comprises of a long hose, velcro fastener, air release valve. Features: User friendly Latex free Long hose How to use the Cuff efficiently: Wrap the cuff around the patient's arm and use the INDEX line to make out if the patient's arm circumference is within the targeted area. Wrap the BP cuff snugly around the arm. Right on the same arm that you place the BP cuff, examine the arm at the crease to locate the strongest pulse sound and place the bell of the stethoscope over the brachial artery at this location. Inflate the BP Cuff by pumping the cuff bulb as you listen to the pulse sound. Just when the BP cuff has inflated enough to stop the blood flow, you should hear no sound through stethoscope. The gauge should read 30-40 mmHg above a person's normal BP reading. Gradually deflate the BP cuff by losing the hold on the bulb. It is best learnt that the pressure should fall at 2-3 mmHg per second, anything faster than that may tend to provide a false reading.
